Music legend Bob Dylan has announced two dates in Wolverhampton as part of his upcoming UK tour.The 83-year-old singer-songwriter will be performing at University of Wolverhampton at The Halls on 9 and 10 November.Dylan will also play in Edinburgh, Bournemouth, Liverpool, Nottingham and London as part of the 10-date tour.The shows will be phone-free, with people asked to put away their devices for the duration of the performance.
Dylan is one of the most acclaimed songwriters of all time, winning 10 Grammys and nominated on 38 further occasions.He has had six top-10 singles and nine number one albums in the UK, with hits including Blowin’ in the Wind, The Times they are A-Changin’ and Like a Rolling Stone.
